{"source_type": "idea", "source_id": "platform-dependency-trap", "source_display": "Platform Dependency Trap (LinkedIn Relationship Monopoly)", "relation": "originated_in", "target_type": "meeting", "target_id": "mtg_2026-01-16-2026-01-16-vrijen-attawar-and-asher-king-abramson", "target_display": "V + Asher King Abramson Meeting", "context_meeting_id": "mtg_2026-01-16-2026-01-16-vrijen-attawar-and-asher-king-abramson", "evidence": "Platforms create dependency not because they provide unique value, but because they create monopoly on relationships. LinkedIn's power doesn't come from having the best jobs or the best data. Its power comes from being the sole graph of professional relationships.", "evolution_type": null}
